        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 10:49PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 1048 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Howell, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Dodge City around 1105 PM CDT.

Other locations in the path of this storm include Wright and Ft.
Dodge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
southwestern Kansas.</instruction>
